      • getElementsWithStereotype

        protected static void getElementsWithStereotype(org.eclipse.uml2.uml.Element parent_elt,
                                                Class clazz,
                                                LinkedList<org.eclipse.uml2.uml.NamedElement> target_list)
        Retrieve all sub-elements (of type Class) for a given element that have the provided stereotype. Basically, retrieves all the component models inside a RobotML model.
        Parameters:
        parent_elt - the root element to inspect
        clazz - the stereotype class we are looking for. Usually something like ...RobotML.SensorSystem
        target_list - the list in which the found elements will be stored.

      • getElementsWithStereotype

public static List<org.eclipse.uml2.uml.NamedElement> getElementsWithStereotype(org.eclipse.uml2.uml.Model model,
                                                                                            String stereotype)
        Deprecated. to be replaced with calls to the RobotML API. Replaced by getElementsWithStereotype (Model model, StereotypeClass sc)
        Recursive retrieve of all elements with a given stereotype in the model.
        Parameters:
        model - Model to search in.
        stereotype - The stereotype name (e.g. "Sensor", "Actuator", "SubSystem"...)
        Returns:
        A list of NamedElements having the specified stereotype.
